<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-01-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="128" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/1–1746</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Committee of
                                    Three</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Executive
                                    Headquarters</gloss></hi><note n="67" xml:id="d128fn67">Copy
                                transmitted to the Secretary of State by General Marshall with
                                covering memorandum of January 17; received January
                            31.</note></head>
                        <p>We, General Chang Chun, authorized representative of the National
                            Government; General Chou En-lai, authorized representative of the
                            Chinese Communist Party and General of the Army George C. Marshall do
                            hereby instruct the Commissioners of the Executive Headquarters to
                            dispatch immediately a group of three representatives to Jehol and
                            Chahar to report on conditions as they exist at that time.</p>
                        <closer><signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chang Chun</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chou En-lai</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">G. C. Marshall</hi>
                            </signed>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-01-14">14 January
                                1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>